    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-03-27T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-03-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="34"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d34">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Uhl</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Smythe</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-03-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 27, 1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 88.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to Department’s No. 82, of the 7th
                    instant, and previous instructions in regard to the case of Bernard Campbell
                    against Haiti, I inclose affidavits of John J. Man ton, John Kelly, and George
                    Nagle, transmitted in Mr. Campbell’s letter of the 25th instant, the statements
                    of which corroborate those made in Mr. Campbell’s memorial and the other
                    affidavits forwarded with it.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edwin F. Uhl</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>(Inclosures: Copies of inclosures in letter of B. Campbell, March 25,
                            1895.<note n="1" xml:id="d34fn1">Not printed.</note>)</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
